sentences: Daan Romers (Dutch pronunciation: [daːn ˈromərs]; born 10 November 1985), better known by his stage name Dannic, is a Dutch DJ and EDM producer.
As of 2013, he has a radio show called Front of House.
He started his career in 2009 and became famous off the Dancetour remix competition for Dutch deep house artist Funkerman, with a track he made with Shermanology titled 'Automatic.'
In 2014 his place changed drastically by becoming the #30 DJ in the world following his best friend Dyro's #30 spot in 2013.
In 2015, Dannic was ranked #26 best DJ in the world, ahead of Dyro by one spot.
On 13 October 2015 he announced the creation of his own independent label Fonk Recordings, named after his 2015 track Fonk which was released under Hardwell's label Revealed Recordings.
